detaileddescription.para:
channel



The channel to execute the command.



cmd



The command to execute (e.g. "ls ~/ -al | grep -i reports").



SSH_OK on success, SSH_ERROR if an error occurred, SSH_AGAIN if in nonblocking mode and call has to be done again.
Example: rc=channel_request_exec(channel,"psaux");
if(rc>0){
return-1;
}

while((rc=channel_read(channel,buffer,sizeof(buffer),0))>0){
if(fwrite(buffer,1,rc,stdout)!=(unsignedint)rc){
return-1;
}
}

channel



The channel to send the eof to.



SSH_OK on success, SSH_ERROR if an error occurred.
Example: rc=ssh_channel_send_eof(channel);
if(rc==SSH_ERROR){
return-1;
}
while(!ssh_channel_is_eof(channel)){
rc=ssh_channel_read(channel,buf,sizeof(buf),0);
if(rc==SSH_ERROR){
return-1;
}
}
ssh_channel_close(channel);

listitem.para:
SSH_OPTIONS_STATUS_CALLBACK: Set a callback to show connection status in realtime (function pointer).

fn(void*arg,floatstatus)

 During ssh_connect(), libssh will call the callback with status from 0.0 to 1.0.
